parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants may not receive the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
even when the vehicle is traveling at a moderate speed
the airbag warning indicator illuminates
and the system may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwanted airbag deployment can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, as the driver may be startled or lose control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbags deploy unexpectedly
even when the vehicle is not involved in a crash
the driver may be startled
and the vehicle may be damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag system malfunction can lead to false warnings, unwanted deployments, or failure to deploy in the event of a crash, which can compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: The airbag warning indicator illuminates
the airbag system needs to be replaced
and there may be a defect in the driver's side airbag.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, and can also result in unpredictable braking performance, which can compromise safety.
symptoms: ABS light is on and off
pumping noise when pressing the brakes
steering wheel shakes drastically at high speed when braking
and the brakes work only half of the time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the vehicle may not be able to stop in time or may lose control.
symptoms: Brake pads failed
warped rotors causing brakes to shake/vibrate
and the vehicle does not slow down or stop when the brake pedal is depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uncontrolled acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the vehicle may lose control and crash.
symptoms: The vehicle lurches and the engine RPM increases rapidly
making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle
and the brakes may not be able to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or quit while in operation, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly quits or stalls while in operation
the vehicle will not start
the ignition switch feels loose or worn out
the ignition switch has a burning smell or smoke.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical wiring harness can cause a fire, potentially leading to serious injury or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Smoke or flames coming from under the hood
a burning smell or odor inside the vehicle
electrical issues or malfunctioning of vehicle systems.
